        <section>
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Voting is a fundamental right and responsibility in a democracy. Understanding the process of voter registration and the history of voting rights is essential for civic engagement.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>History of Voting Rights</h2>
            <p>The right to vote has evolved over time through various amendments and laws, such as the 15th Amendment, the 19th Amendment, and the Voting Rights Act of 1965.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>How to Register to Vote</h2>
            <p>Voter registration can be done online, by mail, or in person. Each state has its own deadlines and requirements.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Barriers to Voting</h2>
            <p>Some voters face obstacles such as voter ID laws, limited polling places, and gerrymandering, which can impact voter turnout.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Why Your Vote Matters</h2>
            <p>Voting influences policies, laws, and leadership at all levels of government. Every vote contributes to shaping the future.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
